{"topicSections":[{"title":"Protocols","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PreferenceKey"],"anchor":"Protocols"},{"title":"Storage","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PreferenceValues"],"anchor":"Storage"}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Preferences","roleHeading":"API Collection"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass data from child views up to their ancestors."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit’s preference system enables "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"bottom-up data flow","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the reverse of environment values. While the environment passes data down from parent to child, preferences let child views publish values that ancestors can observe and react to."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system mirrors SwiftUI’s preference API and consists of three parts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PreferenceKey","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"text":": Protocol that defines a named value type with a default and a reduce strategy","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PreferenceValues","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Type-safe storage that holds all preference values for a scope","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"PreferenceStorage","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":": Stack-based collector that manages preference contexts per render pass","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A built-in example is "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":": a child view sets "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".navigationTitle(\"Settings\")"},{"type":"text","text":", and the enclosing navigation container reads that preference to render the title bar."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Defining a Preference Key","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Defining-a-Preference-Key"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A preference key declares what type of value it carries and how multiple values from sibling children are combined:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct CounterKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: Int = 0","","    static func reduce(value: inout Int, nextValue: () -> Int) {","        value += nextValue()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"defaultValue"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Returned when no child has set this preference","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"reduce(value:nextValue:)","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Combines values when multiple children set the same key"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default "},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation simply takes the last value. Override it when you need additive behavior (summing counts), array collection, or other merge strategies."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Setting a Preference","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Setting-a-Preference"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Child views publish a preference using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".preference(key:value:)"},{"text":" modifier:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ItemView: View {","    var body: some View {","        Text(\"Item\")","            .preference(key: CounterKey.self, value: 1)","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Under the hood, this wraps the view in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"text":" that calls ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preferences.setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"text":" during rendering. The value is reduced into the current scope using the key’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Observing Preferences","anchor":"Observing-Preferences","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ancestor views react to collected preferences using ","type":"text"},{"code":".onPreferenceChange(_:perform:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ItemList: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","        }","        .onPreferenceChange(CounterKey.self) { totalCount in","            \/\/ totalCount == 3 (three children each set value: 1, additive reduce)","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier pushes a new preference context, renders all children (which set their preferences), pops the context, and fires the callback with the accumulated result.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"The Navigation Title Shortcut","anchor":"The-Navigation-Title-Shortcut","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit provides "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a built-in preference key with a convenience modifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct SettingsPage: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Text(\"App settings go here\")","        }","        .navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"NavigationTitleKey","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" uses the default ","type":"text"},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (last value wins), so the deepest child’s title takes precedence.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"How-Preferences-Flow-per-Frame","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How Preferences Flow per Frame"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Preferences are collected fresh every frame. Here’s the lifecycle within a single render pass:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Reset","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"code":"RenderLoop.render()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" calls "},{"code":"preferences.beginRenderPass()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", clearing all callbacks and resetting the stack to a single empty context"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Set","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": As the view tree renders top-down, ","type":"text"},{"code":"PreferenceModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" views call ","type":"text"},{"code":"setValue(_:forKey:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which reduces values into the current stack frame","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OnPreferenceChangeModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" pushes a new context before rendering its subtree, isolating child preferences"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Collect","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": After the subtree finishes, the modifier pops the context (merging into the parent) and fires the callback with the scoped result","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Discard"}]},{"type":"text","text":": At the start of the next frame, everything resets: stale preferences never persist"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This per-frame reset ensures preferences always reflect the current view tree. Removed views stop contributing automatically."}]},{"anchor":"Reduce-Strategies","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Reduce Strategies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function determines how multiple children’s values combine. Common patterns:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategy"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use Case","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Last value wins"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"value = nextValue()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (default)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Titles, labels: deepest child wins","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Additive","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value += nextValue()"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Counting items, summing heights"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Array collection","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"value.append(contentsOf: nextValue())","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gathering menu items, breadcrumbs"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"codeListing","sy